00:00:51.910 --> 00:00:53.650 align:middle line:10%
In our earlier
discussion, when we

00:00:53.650 --> 00:00:56.620 align:middle line:10%
talked about the Vedic
tradition, the Sanskrit

00:00:56.620 --> 00:01:01.780 align:middle line:10%
tradition, we discussed many
elegant metaphysical ideas,

00:01:01.780 --> 00:01:05.620 align:middle line:10%
such as the idea that
Atman equals Brahman

00:01:05.620 --> 00:01:10.000 align:middle line:10%
that the very essence of
the individual human being

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.330 align:middle line:10%
is the same as the
totality of the universe,

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:15.910 align:middle line:10%
as the supreme deity.

00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:19.120 align:middle line:84%
But when we look
at the yoga sutras,

00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:23.200 align:middle line:84%
it seems as if here, we
find something very unique--

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:27.310 align:middle line:84%
not only an elegant
philosophy but a technology

00:01:27.310 --> 00:01:32.380 align:middle line:84%
by which we can achieve
these remarkable insights

00:01:32.380 --> 00:01:35.660 align:middle line:84%
and integrate them
into our lives.

00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:42.970 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes, the yoga sutras
are a how-to manual.

00:01:42.970 --> 00:01:46.630 align:middle line:10%
Given this cosmology
that we've talked about

00:01:46.630 --> 00:01:48.610 align:middle line:10%
and what the universe
is like and what

00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:52.240 align:middle line:10%
you're like in it that
we get from the Veda,

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:55.930 align:middle line:10%
then how shall we proceed?

00:01:55.930 --> 00:02:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And the Patanjali
sutras are a manual

00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:07.580 align:middle line:90%
of just how to get there.

00:02:07.580 --> 00:02:08.380 align:middle line:90%
Very practical.

00:02:08.380 --> 00:02:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> And as I understand it, one
of the key insights is very

00:02:11.300 --> 00:02:12.100 align:middle line:90%
simple.

00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:14.920 align:middle line:84%
By quieting the
mind, by reducing

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:18.340 align:middle line:84%
the chatter of the mind,
when the mind is still,

00:02:18.340 --> 00:02:23.800 align:middle line:84%
it can then be a perfect
reflection of reality.

00:02:23.800 --> 00:02:26.200 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:30.610 align:middle line:84%
In Sanskrit, the mind is
called the chit or the chitta.

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And the thoughts and sensations
are waves in the mind.

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:40.510 align:middle line:84%
It sounds like creating your
quantum mechanics of waves

00:02:40.510 --> 00:02:43.630 align:middle line:90%
and physics, wave mechanics.

00:02:43.630 --> 00:02:46.780 align:middle line:90%
The mind operates by waves.

00:02:46.780 --> 00:02:48.890 align:middle line:90%
These are called the Vritti.

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:51.940 align:middle line:84%
So we have Vritti
and the chitta.

00:02:51.940 --> 00:02:59.290 align:middle line:84%
And meditation is the process of
stilling the waves in the mind,

00:02:59.290 --> 00:03:03.560 align:middle line:84%
so the mind can be the perfect
reflection of the universe

00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:04.845 align:middle line:90%
and everything that's in it.

00:03:04.845 --> 00:03:08.620 align:middle line:84%
>> And we talked in our earlier
program about the concept

00:03:08.620 --> 00:03:14.150 align:middle line:84%
of Ritam-bhara pragya,
the realm of perfection,

00:03:14.150 --> 00:03:18.490 align:middle line:84%
which is a level of
consciousness, in effect.

00:03:18.490 --> 00:03:21.200 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's even
beyond consciousness.

00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.130 align:middle line:84%
It's the place where
things are perfect.

00:03:24.130 --> 00:03:29.150 align:middle line:84%
And consciousness can
access these, and in a way,

00:03:29.150 --> 00:03:32.020 align:middle line:84%
if we take a certain
definition of consciousness,

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:36.860 align:middle line:84%
that would also include
this field of ideals.

00:03:36.860 --> 00:03:42.670 align:middle line:84%
But one apprehends the
perfect by stilling

00:03:42.670 --> 00:03:47.110 align:middle line:84%
all the waves in the mind
and pointing the mind

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:49.480 align:middle line:90%
toward the object of attention.

00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:54.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Now in the yoga sutras,
there are various stages

00:03:54.580 --> 00:03:58.150 align:middle line:90%
in the development of a yogi.

00:03:58.150 --> 00:04:02.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, there are many
stages and many paths.

00:04:02.570 --> 00:04:07.840 align:middle line:84%
In the yoga sutras,
there are four stages

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:13.150 align:middle line:84%
called, in that book,
pada, pedal, foot.

00:04:13.150 --> 00:04:15.970 align:middle line:90%
A pada is a foot.

00:04:15.970 --> 00:04:18.370 align:middle line:90%
So there are four feet.

00:04:18.370 --> 00:04:23.950 align:middle line:84%
The last one is Kavya,
which is usually translated

00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:27.520 align:middle line:90%
as liberation, freedom.

00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:32.920 align:middle line:84%
But the word really means
isolation, aloneness.

00:04:32.920 --> 00:04:36.730 align:middle line:84%
If you achieve total
isolation in the universe

00:04:36.730 --> 00:04:42.050 align:middle line:84%
with no connection to anything
else, then you're free.

00:04:42.050 --> 00:04:46.360 align:middle line:84%
The condition in Sanskrit
is called Samadhi.

00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:51.760 align:middle line:84%
You achieve a place in your
mind where there are no waves.

00:04:51.760 --> 00:04:54.580 align:middle line:84%
You are not connected
to anything else.

00:04:54.580 --> 00:04:57.460 align:middle line:90%
And then you transcend.

00:04:57.460 --> 00:04:59.740 align:middle line:84%
>> In other words, if I
understand it correctly,

00:04:59.740 --> 00:05:02.440 align:middle line:84%
you're free from
karmic attachments.

00:05:02.440 --> 00:05:05.340 align:middle line:90%


00:05:05.340 --> 00:05:07.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, yes.

00:05:07.890 --> 00:05:17.340 align:middle line:10%
Karma is a Sanskrit word
meaning work, to do something.

00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:20.490 align:middle line:10%
Your karma is what
you have done.

00:05:20.490 --> 00:05:25.230 align:middle line:10%
So the scars on your body are
results of what you've done.

00:05:25.230 --> 00:05:28.500 align:middle line:84%
And to be free of
karmic attachment

00:05:28.500 --> 00:05:32.920 align:middle line:84%
means to be free of anything
you've ever done before,

00:05:32.920 --> 00:05:34.770 align:middle line:84%
which means that
you have achieved

00:05:34.770 --> 00:05:38.623 align:middle line:84%
that state of Tabula Rasa,
where you're absolutely nothing.

00:05:38.623 --> 00:05:39.540 align:middle line:90%
>> You've, in effect--

00:05:39.540 --> 00:05:41.248 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not necessarily
a desirable fate.

00:05:41.248 --> 00:05:45.930 align:middle line:84%
>> --you've completed
your work, your life.

00:05:45.930 --> 00:05:50.730 align:middle line:84%
>> You've completed all--
you've transcended all memory

00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:52.500 align:middle line:90%
of your life.

00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:58.080 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean that you've
completed your mission in life,

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:01.510 align:middle line:84%
but it means you're
free from all memories.

00:06:01.510 --> 00:06:03.113 align:middle line:84%
>> And you used
the word "scar--"

00:06:03.113 --> 00:06:04.530 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not
necessarily desirable.

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:07.680 align:middle line:84%
>> --earlier, which I believe
relates to the Sanskrit term,

00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:08.550 align:middle line:90%
samskara.

00:06:08.550 --> 00:06:10.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Samskara is a scar, yes.

00:06:10.400 --> 00:06:12.150 align:middle line:84%
That's where we get
our modern word, scar.

00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:15.240 align:middle line:84%
>> And if I understand
that concept correctly,

00:06:15.240 --> 00:06:19.650 align:middle line:84%
the notion is that we are all
constrained by these samskaras.

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:23.790 align:middle line:90%
They represent our conditioning.

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:27.030 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, I don't want
to seem like negative.

00:06:27.030 --> 00:06:28.200 align:middle line:90%
It's a positive.

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:31.210 align:middle line:84%
If you've learned something,
you've conditioned yourself.

00:06:31.210 --> 00:06:35.480 align:middle line:84%
So all learning, all education
is a kind of a conditioning.

00:06:35.480 --> 00:06:40.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's still-- to
re-arrive at this stage

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:44.180 align:middle line:84%
where you have no
samskaras, no conditioning

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:48.600 align:middle line:84%
is at the babe-like state again
where there is no memories.

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:51.700 align:middle line:84%
And then you're fresh
for something new.

00:06:51.700 --> 00:06:52.860 align:middle line:90%
So it's very delicate.

00:06:52.860 --> 00:06:54.795 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to
throw off all karma.

00:06:54.795 --> 00:06:57.810 align:middle line:90%


00:06:57.810 --> 00:07:00.540 align:middle line:84%
You want to take
advantage of what

00:07:00.540 --> 00:07:02.910 align:middle line:90%
you've gained at this point.

00:07:02.910 --> 00:07:04.800 align:middle line:90%
You want to have memories.

00:07:04.800 --> 00:07:08.430 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand, you
want to be able to erase them.

00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:12.600 align:middle line:10%
>> Now, we think of yoga as
often being equated with Hatha

00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:16.230 align:middle line:10%
yoga or the physical
stretching exercises.

00:07:16.230 --> 00:07:18.870 align:middle line:10%
>> Many kinds of yoga, yes.

00:07:18.870 --> 00:07:21.040 align:middle line:84%
Hatha yoga does
make you feel good.

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:25.890 align:middle line:84%
It's good to stretch
and do the asanas.

00:07:25.890 --> 00:07:26.715 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:07:26.715 --> 00:07:27.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Or postures.

00:07:27.850 --> 00:07:28.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Postures, yeah.

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:29.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, asanas.

00:07:29.690 --> 00:07:33.525 align:middle line:84%
>> Asanas comes from to sit
down, a seat to yourself.

00:07:33.525 --> 00:07:37.440 align:middle line:90%


00:07:37.440 --> 00:07:38.880 align:middle line:90%
Sittings.

00:07:38.880 --> 00:07:48.810 align:middle line:84%
But other kinds of yoga are
doing good deeds, Bhakti yoga,

00:07:48.810 --> 00:07:55.170 align:middle line:84%
saying prayers, life of
reverence, Jnana yoga,

00:07:55.170 --> 00:08:01.350 align:middle line:84%
thinking about this or that and
achieving union-- yoga means

00:08:01.350 --> 00:08:03.240 align:middle line:90%
union with God.

00:08:03.240 --> 00:08:05.970 align:middle line:84%
>> It'd be the equivalent
of our word, yoke."

00:08:05.970 --> 00:08:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Yoke, yes.

00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:11.580 align:middle line:84%
>> We yoke the oxen together,
and it's a way of attaching.

00:08:11.580 --> 00:08:15.180 align:middle line:84%
>> And I yoke myself
to God in yoga.

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:18.510 align:middle line:84%
But the paths of yoga include
the intellectual and good

00:08:18.510 --> 00:08:23.520 align:middle line:84%
deeds, exercises,
actions of many sorts.

00:08:23.520 --> 00:08:25.750 align:middle line:84%
>> And the term you
mentioned earlier, Jnana--

00:08:25.750 --> 00:08:26.550 align:middle line:90%
>> Jnana.

00:08:26.550 --> 00:08:30.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Jnana, the yoga of knowledge,
it's related to our word,

00:08:30.430 --> 00:08:31.230 align:middle line:90%
"knowledge."

00:08:31.230 --> 00:08:36.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, Jnana is the root of
our word, to know, knowledge.

00:08:36.610 --> 00:08:39.749 align:middle line:84%
>> That's why "know" has that
funny spelling with the K.

00:08:39.749 --> 00:08:40.549 align:middle line:90%
>> K, yeah.

00:08:40.549 --> 00:08:41.620 align:middle line:90%
Gnosis-- G in gnosis.

00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:44.870 align:middle line:90%


00:08:44.870 --> 00:08:48.840 align:middle line:84%
To know something, to comprehend
something, to really master it.

00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:53.340 align:middle line:84%
>> So there is a sense in which,
when we look at the Sanskrit

00:08:53.340 --> 00:08:58.770 align:middle line:84%
traditions, we get to the very
essential original meanings

00:08:58.770 --> 00:09:01.740 align:middle line:84%
of many of the
words that we use.

00:09:01.740 --> 00:09:06.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, especially in
our English or European

00:09:06.510 --> 00:09:08.700 align:middle line:90%
or Indo-European culture.

00:09:08.700 --> 00:09:12.390 align:middle line:84%
We get back to the
clear original meanings

00:09:12.390 --> 00:09:15.660 align:middle line:84%
of our everyday
dialect in Sanskrit.

00:09:15.660 --> 00:09:19.260 align:middle line:84%
>> So for example, the
discussion that you and I are

00:09:19.260 --> 00:09:22.920 align:middle line:84%
now having is probably,
in a very real sense,

00:09:22.920 --> 00:09:25.230 align:middle line:90%
a form of yoga.

00:09:25.230 --> 00:09:26.570 align:middle line:90%
>> It is, indeed.

00:09:26.570 --> 00:09:28.890 align:middle line:84%
We're studying the
origins of our words

00:09:28.890 --> 00:09:32.610 align:middle line:84%
and crystallizing our
thoughts by so doing.

00:09:32.610 --> 00:09:38.610 align:middle line:84%
That's why Veda is a science,
because it leads to precision.

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:43.380 align:middle line:84%
>> And the technique of
meditation is one that it's not

00:09:43.380 --> 00:09:46.270 align:middle line:84%
just for relaxation
and for health.

00:09:46.270 --> 00:09:50.850 align:middle line:84%
It's actually a very
precise way of attuning

00:09:50.850 --> 00:09:51.980 align:middle line:90%
one's mind so that--

00:09:51.980 --> 00:09:53.355 align:middle line:84%
>> It's fastening
the mind, yeah.

00:09:53.355 --> 00:09:57.630 align:middle line:84%
>> --these abstract metaphysical
concepts become like workable

00:09:57.630 --> 00:09:58.740 align:middle line:90%
tools.

00:09:58.740 --> 00:10:05.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, in one way, it's a
way of creating something.

00:10:05.710 --> 00:10:08.800 align:middle line:84%
I can create something
by putting my mind on it,

00:10:08.800 --> 00:10:17.350 align:middle line:84%
by focusing on it, by allowing
the thought waves of my mind

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:20.950 align:middle line:84%
to go out and grasp the
object of attention,

00:10:20.950 --> 00:10:25.390 align:middle line:84%
by taking the perfect form
in the Ritam Bhara Pragyan,

00:10:25.390 --> 00:10:30.700 align:middle line:84%
and expressing it in
nature, in Prakriti.

00:10:30.700 --> 00:10:33.688 align:middle line:84%
It is the way to
accomplish anything.

00:10:33.688 --> 00:10:35.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Dean, we're going
to take a short break.

