We're talking about
the Sanskrit tradition

00:10:51.890 --> 00:10:55.790 align:middle line:84%
with Dean Brown, a theoretical
physicist, Sanskrit scholar,

00:10:55.790 --> 00:11:00.230 align:middle line:84%
and translator of the
Upanishads and the yoga sutras.

00:11:00.230 --> 00:11:02.930 align:middle line:10%
Dean, one of the really
interesting things to me

00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:05.420 align:middle line:10%
about the yoga
sutras is the idea

00:11:05.420 --> 00:11:10.190 align:middle line:10%
that there are the siddhis,
the powers of the mind that

00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:13.310 align:middle line:10%
become activated through
the practice of yoga

00:11:13.310 --> 00:11:14.480 align:middle line:10%
and meditation.

00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:10%
Not only does the yogi
see reality clearly

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:21.770 align:middle line:10%
both in its physical and
metaphysical dimensions,

00:11:21.770 --> 00:11:27.290 align:middle line:10%
but many abilities that we would
call in the West psychic powers

00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:29.930 align:middle line:10%
or the gifts of
the spirit are also

00:11:29.930 --> 00:11:33.980 align:middle line:10%
available through
yoga discipline.

00:11:33.980 --> 00:11:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, because they're
available through the mind

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:43.190 align:middle line:84%
itself, and the yoga discipline
enhances the faculties

00:11:43.190 --> 00:11:46.070 align:middle line:84%
and the capabilities
of the mind.

00:11:46.070 --> 00:11:52.430 align:middle line:84%
All mental powers can
be accessed and improved

00:11:52.430 --> 00:11:54.380 align:middle line:90%
through the practice of yoga.

00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:59.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Because to the yogis,
the mind over and above--

00:11:59.120 --> 00:12:01.910 align:middle line:84%
you use the term the
"chit," the thoughts,

00:12:01.910 --> 00:12:03.860 align:middle line:84%
the activity of the
mind is one thing,

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:06.920 align:middle line:84%
but the mind itself
contains this activity.

00:12:06.920 --> 00:12:12.680 align:middle line:84%
And it's equated, if I recall
correctly, with the divine.

00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:18.190 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes, in Veda, everything
is divine in the end.

00:12:18.190 --> 00:12:26.960 align:middle line:10%
And the mind or consciousness
is the ultimate fabric

00:12:26.960 --> 00:12:28.680 align:middle line:10%
of the divine.

00:12:28.680 --> 00:12:36.110 align:middle line:10%
So by gaining control of the
mind or your mind or my mind,

00:12:36.110 --> 00:12:39.770 align:middle line:10%
we access everything.

00:12:39.770 --> 00:12:41.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything unfolds
from the mind, in effect.

00:12:41.960 --> 00:12:44.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything unfolds
from the mind.

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:47.270 align:middle line:84%
Now that isn't such a strange
idea for modern psychology

00:12:47.270 --> 00:12:49.520 align:middle line:90%
that everything is in the mind.

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:58.370 align:middle line:84%
But in the Veda, it's a very
practical and useful concept

00:12:58.370 --> 00:13:01.430 align:middle line:90%
and pursuit.

00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:04.730 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's an idea that, today,
